# Task 14: Ensemble Methods - Bagging and Boosting

**PKCERT AI & Software Development Internship**

This project explores ensemble learning techniques for classification tasks using the Bank Marketing dataset. Bagging and Boosting methods are implemented and rigorously compared.

## Project Objectives
- Implement Bagging using Random Forest
- Implement Boosting using XGBoost
- Evaluate models using standard classification metrics
- Provide comparative analysis and business recommendation

## Dataset
The Bank Marketing dataset from UCI contains information from direct marketing campaigns of a Portuguese banking institution. The goal is to predict whether a client will subscribe to a term deposit (binary classification).

## Methodology
- Data preprocessing using ColumnTransformer pipeline
- Bagging with Random Forest Classifier
- Boosting with XGBoost Classifier
- Performance evaluation using Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, and ROC-AUC where applicable

## Results Summary
Both ensemble methods achieved strong performance (~92% accuracy). XGBoost demonstrated marginally better results, particularly on the minority class, highlighting its effectiveness for this type of tabular data.

## Technologies Used
- Python 3
- scikit-learn
- XGBoost
- pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn

